history.content: I took 182 and 189 concurrently last spring (182 for a letter grade and 189 P/NP). I didn't feel like things from 189 were particularly needed for 182, especially since you'll have other background in probability/optimization/linear algebra fundamentals. 182 will help with the last homework in 189.

children.subject: Agreed, taking them concurrently worked quite well for me, and when you do get to the neural nets part of 189, things will feel very familiar.

history.content:
Currently, I'm a senior taking EE127 and CS189, with a special topic and a psychology class.

I'm thinking to drop 189 this semester and take it Spring 2020 since I don't feel like I'm completely ready for the optimization part of 189.

I also don't think later on I will have enough time to tackle all the 189 homework questions and digest the massive content when the potential interviews are coming in.

I'm thinking about auditing 189 for this semester, then take 182 and 189 together next semester. I looked through the piazza. There are different opinion on whether or not we need to finish 189 before 182, and those comments are all several semesters ago.

I hope I can get some new comments on taking 182 and 189 (Shewchuk's) together, and what kind of preparation to make during the winter break. Any inputs are appreciated!!

For my background, I took 53, 54, 16AB, 110, DS100 and 126 with decent grades. I'm taking 127 this semester (and planning to audit 189's lecture and try my best to follow up with the discussion, but not homework).
